# Dist (but keep the folder structure if committed, usually binaries are ignored but sometimes kept for submission. 
# Prompt implied "order project like this" for submission, so I will NOT ignore the JARs in dist if they want to see them there, 
# BUT standard practice is to ignore. The user said "order my project like this", implying the result. 
# I will ignore the jar files themselves to be safe for a repo, but the user can force add them if needed. 
# Actually, for University submissions often they want the jars. 
# I will leave dist/ commented out so they are tracked if generated and added, or explicitly ignore specific things.
# I'll just ignore standard build artifacts.